headline: P&C Insurance Industry Sees Digital Capabilities Gap Shrink between Top Performers and Broader Market, Says New Research
summary: The property and casualty insurance industry has reached a point of competitive convergence, with all 20 carriers evaluated in Corporate Insight's 2025 P&C Insurance Experience Benchmark clustering in the middle tiers (Achieving or Effective). In the third edition of the annual benchmarking report, no insurers finished in either the lowest or highest tiers, signaling that digital laggards have caught up while front-runners have yet to pull decisively ahead.

headline: 3 Cash-Producing Stocks with Open Questions
summary: A company that generates cash isn’t automatically a winner. Some businesses stockpile cash but fail to reinvest wisely, limiting their ability to expand.
